","meta":[{"id":"target","value":"_blank"}],"type":"link","children":[{"type":"span","value":"Gatsby"}]},{"type":"span","value":" blog and DatoCMS which is the headless CMS used in my blog."}]},{"type":"list","style":"bulleted","children":[{"type":"listItem","children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"span","marks":["highlight"],"value":"The frontend codes"},{"type":"span","value":"(Gatsby)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"span","marks":["highlight"],"value":"The contents posted on the blog"},{"type":"span","value":"(DatoCMS)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"span","marks":["highlight"],"value":"CMS to frontend communication method"},{"type":"span","value":"(GraphQL)"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"span","value":"You can select the frontend framework whatever you want because the frontend codes just need to draw how to show the contents on the website. Since the contents which are posted on the blog are managed by external CMS, the contents and the frontend codes are completely separated. "}]},{"type":"thematicBreak"},{"type":"heading","level":2,"children":[{"type":"span","value":"How does the Headless CMS work?"}]},{"item":"10393792","type":"block"},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"span","value":"Then, how do we get the contents from the CMS when we deploy the blog? "},{"type":"span","marks":["highlight"],"value":"Generally"},{"type":"span","value":", as you may thought, it can be done with "},{"type":"span","marks":["highlight"],"value":"RESTful API or GraphQL"},{"type":"span","value":". Posting the new content procedure progresses through the following steps."}]},{"type":"list","style":"numbered","children":[{"type":"listItem","children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"span","value":"Writing new contents on the CMS"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"span","value":"Deploying the blog("},{"type":"span","marks":["code"],"value":"npm run deploy"},{"type":"span","value":", etc.)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"span","value":"Getting contents from CMS while generate static web page"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"span","value":"Complete deploying static web page blog(Gatsby, Jekyll, etc.) "}]}]}]},{"type":"thematicBreak"},{"type":"heading","level":2,"children":[{"type":"span","value":"Convenience hidden behind a spooky word"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"span","value":"We are not getting scared by the word \"Headless\" anymore unless we saw it in real life!ü§£ After all, the headless CMS is a great tool for people who wants to manage something like blogs flexibly and conveniently. If you are planning to manage new blogs, make fascinating blogs with the headless CMS!"}]},{"item":"10536677","type":"block"}]}}}}},"pageContext":{"id":"6607939","locale":"en"}},"staticQueryHashes":["1034768456","1118752904","2342916782","2757196681","3415878905","3879866231","4195094990"]}